5|$|In 2009 {{she became}} the first {{political}} promoter of the law against stalking offence. This law was finally approved on 23 February 2009, introduced as a package of bills known as the Decreto Maroni. In the same year she signed a campaign against homophobia in Italy, with television spots, images on magazines and wall attachments on cities. She also proposed a bill against homophobia, in which homophobia was considered as an <b>aggravating</b> <b>circumstance</b> in bullying events. This bill was next refused by the Parliament.|$|E
25|$|On May 22, 2007, the Louisiana Supreme Court {{held that}} it is {{constitutional}} to impose {{the death penalty for}} rape if the victim is a child. Ruling on an appeal brought in the case of defendant Patrick Kennedy, Justice Jeffrey Victory wrote for the court that the Louisiana law allowing the imposition of the death penalty under those circumstances was consistent with Coker because an <b>aggravating</b> <b>circumstance,</b> the age of the victim, justified the death penalty.|$|E
