50|$|Medina {{was convicted}} of first-degree murder and auto theft. The jury, by a ten-to-two vote, {{recommended}} {{the death penalty for}} the murder conviction. The trial court found two <b>aggravating</b> <b>circumstances</b>  and a single mitigating circumstance. The court found the <b>aggravating</b> <b>circumstances</b> outweighed the mitigating circumstance and sentenced Medina to death. This Court affirmed Medina's convictions and sentences. (Medina v. State, 466 So.2d 1046 (Fla. 1985)).|$|R
